{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "If the state 𝑠𝑡 (𝑆𝑡𝑜𝑣𝑒𝑂𝑁, 𝑡 𝑠, 𝑡 𝑒) is an inner state in the current window, it is mapped to the sentence \"The subject turned on the stove and turned it off after 𝑡 𝑒 -𝑡 𝑠 seconds\".",
    "When the same state is an Already active state for the current window, the sentence \"The stove is already turned on\" is produced, and if there is another already active state (e.g., about the fridge) the corresponding sentence is combined with the one for the stove.",
    "When the 𝑆𝑡𝑜𝑣𝑒𝑂𝑁 state ends before the end of the window, the following sentence is produced \"After 𝑡 𝑒 -𝑡 seconds the subject turned off the stove\".",
    "As another example, the inner state 𝑠𝑡 (𝑁 𝑒𝑎𝑟 𝐵𝑎𝑡ℎ𝑟𝑜𝑜𝑚𝑆𝑖𝑛𝑘, 𝑡 𝑠, 𝑡 𝑒) generated by a PIR sensor leads to the sentence \"The subject was near the sink for 𝑡 𝑒 -𝑡 𝑠 seconds\".Example 3.2.",
    "Consider a window 𝑤 𝑡 that has associated the Inner states 𝑠𝑡 (𝐹𝑟𝑖𝑑𝑔𝑒𝐷𝑜𝑜𝑟𝑂𝑝𝑒𝑛, 𝑡1, 𝑡2), 𝑠𝑡 (𝑁 𝑒𝑎𝑟𝑆𝑡𝑜𝑣𝑒, 𝑡3, 𝑡4) and a Persistent state 𝑠𝑡 (𝑂𝑛𝑇ℎ𝑒𝐶𝑜𝑢𝑐ℎ, 𝑡5, 𝑡6), where 𝑡2 < 𝑡3, 𝑡4 < 𝑡5, and 𝑡6 > 𝑡 + 𝜏. ADL-LLM automatically infers (using simple rules) that 𝐹𝑟𝑖𝑑𝑔𝑒𝐷𝑜𝑜𝑟 and 𝑁 𝑒𝑎𝑟𝑆𝑡𝑜𝑣𝑒 occurred consecutively in kitchen, and after the subject moves to the living room for the 𝑂𝑛𝑇ℎ𝑒𝐶𝑜𝑢𝑐ℎ state."
  ],
